fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with personal questions and comments addressed to passersby: </div><div class="t m6c6 xb h1e y8af ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Sir, did you know that the wages of sin is death?&quot; &quot;Madam, if </div><div class="t m6c7 xb h1e y8b0 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">you give your heart to Jesus, you will find peace.&quot; A manicured </div><div class="t m6c8 xb h1e y8b1 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">gentleman dressed in a tweed suit commented as he hurried by, </div><div class="t m5e8 xb h1e y8b2 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Your technique is terrible, but your reasoning from cause to effect </div><div class="t m270 xb h1e y8b3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">is flawless.&quot; </div><div class="t m9 x5 h1e y2e6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus was the great proclaimer of spiritual cause and effect. For </div><div class="t m148 xb h1e y30b ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">example, He said, &quot;Judge not, that ye be not judged&quot; (Matt. 7:1); </div><div class="t m45e xb h1e y8b4 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;For whosoever exalteth himself shall be abased&quot; (Luke 14:11). </div><div class="t m6c9 x67 h1e y8b5 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Peter also deals with cause and effect. &quot;Do not return evil for </div><div class="t m6ca xb h1e y67e ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">evil . . . that you may obtain a blessing&quot; (1 Peter 3:9, RSV). &quot;But </div><div class="t m6cb xb h1e y8b6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">even if you do suffer for righteousness&apos; sake, you will be blessed&quot; </div><div class="t m6cc xb h1e y8b7 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 14, RSV). </div><div class="t m400 xa2 h1e y8b8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">69 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
